  = \n<!-- Population   ----------------------->\n|population_as_of                = \n|population_footnotes            =\n|population_note                 =\n|population_total                =\n|population_density_km2          =  <!--For automatic calculation, any density field may contain: auto -->\n|population_metro                =\n|population_density_metro_km2    =\n|population_urban                =\n|population_density_urban_km2    =\n|population_blank1_title         =\n|population_blank1               =\n|population_density_blank1_km2   =   \n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = [[China Standard Time|China Standard]]\n|utc_offset             = +8\n|coordinates            = {{coord|41|34|N|108|32|E|type:adm3rd_region:CN-15_source:kolossus-dewiki|display=inline,title}}\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       = Postal code <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            = \n|area_code              =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              =  \n}}\n\n'''Urad Middle Banner''' ([[Mongolian language|Mongolian]]: {{MongolUnicode|\u1824\u1837\u1820\u1833\u202f\u1824\u1828}} {{MongolUnicode|\u1833\u1824\u182e\u1833\u1820\u1833\u1824}} {{MongolUnicode|\u182c\u1823\u1830\u1822\u182d\u1824}} \u0423\u0440\u0430\u0434-\u0443\u043d \u0414\u0443\u043c\u0434\u0430\u0434\u0443 \u049a\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0443 ''Urad-un Dumdadu Qosi\u0263u''; {{zh|s=\u4e4c\u62c9\u7279\u4e2d\u65d7 |t=\u70cf\u62c9\u7279\u4e2d\u65d7 |p=W\u016bl\u0101t\u00e8 Zh\u014dng Q\u00ed}}) is a [[Banner (Inner Mongolia)|banner]] of the [[Inner Mongolia]] Autonomous Region, [[People's Republic of China]]. It is located in the west of the region, and administratively is part of [[Bayan Nur]] City. It has a total area of {{convert|22,606|km\u00b2}} and in 2004 had a population of 140,000. Its seat is located in the town of {{ill|Haliut|zh|\u6d77\u6d41\u56fe\u9547}} ({{lang|zh-Hans|\u6d77\u6d41\u56fe\u9547}}).\n\n==Climate==\nUrad Middle Banner has a [[monsoon]]-influenced, [[continentality|continental]] [[semi-arid climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]] ''BSk''), barely avoiding [[arid climate|arid]] designation, with very cold and dry winters, hot, somewhat humid summers, and strong winds, especially in spring. The monthly 24-hour average temperature ranges from {{convert|\u221213.3|\u00b0C|1}} in January to {{convert|22.9|\u00b0C|1}} in July, with the annual mean at {{convert|5.75|\u00b0C|1}}. The annual precipitation is {{convert|199|mm|in|abbr=on}}, with more than half of it falling in July and August alone. With monthly percent possible sunshine ranging from 65% in July to 76% in October, sunshine is abundant year-round, and there are 3,164 hours of bright sunshine annually.\n\n{{Weather box\n|location = Urad Middle Banner (1981\u22122010 normals)\n|metric first = Y\n|single line = Y\n|collapsed =\n|Jan high C = \u22126.5\n|Feb high C = \u22121.5\n|Mar high C =  6.0\n|Apr high C = 15.0\n|May high C = 22.2\n|Jun high C = 27.0\n|Jul high C = 28.9\n|Aug high C = 26.3\n|Sep high C = 21.1\n|Oct high C = 13.2\n|Nov high C =  2.9\n|Dec high C = \u22124.9\n\n|Jan mean C = \u221213.3\n|Feb mean C =  \u22128.7\n|Mar mean C =  \u22121.2\n|Apr mean C =   7.9\n|May mean C =  15.4\n|Jun mean C =  20.7\n|Jul mean C =  22.9\n|Aug mean C =  20.4\n|Sep mean C =  14.4\n|Oct mean C =   5.9\n|Nov mean C =  \u22124.1\n|Dec mean C = \u221211.3\n\n|Jan low C = \u221218.5\n|Feb low C = \u221214.3\n|Mar low C =  \u22127.4\n|Apr low C =   0.8\n|May low C =   8.2\n|Jun low C =  13.7\n|Jul low C =  16.7\n|Aug low C =  14.5\n|Sep low C =   8.2\n|Oct low C =   0.0\n|Nov low C =  \u22129.1\n|Dec low C = \u221216.2\n|precipitation colour = green\n|Jan precipitation mm =  1.6\n|Feb precipitation mm =  1.7\n|Mar precipitation mm =  4.0\n|Apr precipitation mm =  3.9\n|May precipitation mm = 14.8\n|Jun precipitation mm = 25.8\n|Jul precipitation mm = 51.3\n|Aug precipitat