yan]]''\n*2006 ''[[Tom, Dick, and Harry (2006 film)|Tom Dick And Harry]]''\n*2007 ''[[Marigold (2007 film)|Marigold]]''\n*2007 ''[[Just Married (2007 film)|Just Married]]''\n*2007 ''[[Delhii Heights]]''\n*2007 ''[[Good Boy, Bad Boy]]''\n*2007 ''[[The Train (2007 film)|The Train]]''\n*2007 ''[[MP3: Mera Pehla Pehla Pyaar]]''\n*2007 ''[[Awarapan]]''\n*2007 ''[[Cash (2007 film)|Cash]]''\n*2007 ''[[Darling (2007 Indian film)|Darling]]''\n*2007 ''[[Chhodon Naa Yaar]]''\n*2007 ''[[Speed (2007 film)|Speed]]''\n*2007 ''Main Rony Aur Jony''\n*2008 ''[[Mithya]]''\n*2008 ''[[Singh Is Kinng]]''\n*2008 ''[[Bhoothnath]]''\n*2008 ''[[De Taali]]''\n*2008 ''[[Mission Istaanbul]]''\n*2008 ''[[Ugly Aur Pagli]]''\n*2008 ''[[Rock On!!]]''\n*2008 ''[[Hijack (2008 film)|Hijack]]''\n*2008 ''[[Kidnap (2008 film)|Kidnap]]''\n*2008 ''[[Sorry Bhai!]]''\n*2008 ''[[Maharathi (2008 film)|Maharathi]]''\n*2009 ''[[The Stoneman Murders]]''\n*2009 ''[[Kal Kissne Dekha]]''\n*2009 ''[[London Dreams]]''\n*2009 ''[[Mr. Fraud]]''\n*2010 ''[[Enthiran]]''\n*2011 ''[[Patiala House]]''\n*2011 ''[[F.A.L.T.U]]''\n*2011 ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama]]''\n*2011 ''[[Kucch Luv Jaisaa]]''\n*2011 ''[[Bbuddah... Hoga Terra Baap]]''\n*2011 ''Stand By''\n*2011 ''[[Love Breakups Zindagi]]''\n*2011 ''[[Loot (2011 film)|Loot]]''\n*2012 ''[[Student of the Year]]''\n*2013 ''[[ABCD: Any Body Can Dance]]''\n*2013 ''[[Zila Ghaziabad]]''\n*2013 ''[[Aurangzeb]]''\n*2013 ''[[Besharam (2013 film)|Besharam]]''\n*2013 ''[[Krrish 3]]''\n*2013 ''[[Gori Tere Pyaar Mein]]''\n*2013 ''[[Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani]]''\n*2014 ''[[Dedh Ishqiya]]''\n*2014 ''[[2 States (2014 film)|2 States]]''\n*2014 ''[[Jai Ho (film)|Jai Ho]]''\n*2014 ''[[Entertainment]]''\n*2014 ''[[O Teri]]''\n*2014 ''[[Familywala]]''\n*2015 ''[[Tevar]]''\n*2015 ''[[ABCD 2]]''\n*2015 ''[[Bajrangi Bhaijaan]]''\n*2015 ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]''\n*2015 ''[[Dilwale (2015 film)|Dilwale]]''\n*2016 ''[[A Flying Jatt]]''\n*2018 ''[[Race 3]]''\n*2018 ''[[Zero (2018 film)|Zero]]''\n*2019 ''[[Kalank]]''\n*2019 ''[[Student of the Year 2]]''\n*2020 ''[[Street Dancer 3D]]''\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Television===\n* ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' ([[Dance India Dance#Season 1|season 1]]) with [[Geeta Kapoor]] & [[Terence Lewis (choreographer)|Terrence Lewis]]\n* ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' ([[Dance India Dance#Season 2|season 2]]) with Geeta Kapoor & Terrence Lewis\n* ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 4]]'' with [[Madhuri Dixit]] & [[Malaika Arora Khan]]\n* ''[[Dance India Dance Doubles]]'' as a guest judge\n* ''[[Dance Ke Superstars]]'' with [[Shiamak Davar]]\n* ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' ([[Dance India Dance#Season 3|season 3]]) with [[Geeta Kapoor]] & [[Terence Lewis (choreographer)|Terrence Lewis]]\n* ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 5]]'' with Madhuri Dixit & [[Karan Johar]]\n* ''[[Comedy Circus Ke Ajoobe]]'' as a guest judge\n* ''[[Nach Baliye 5]]'' as a guest judge\n* ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 6]]'' with Madhuri Dixit & Karan Johar\n* ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa (season 7)|Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 7]]'' with Madhuri Dixit & Karan Johar\n* ''[[Dance Plus]]'', Season 1 (2015)<ref>{{cite web |title=Judges, Hosts, Contestants : Dance Plus 2015 |url=http://danceplus.co.in/judges-hosts-contestants-dance-plus-2015/ |date=2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150728205357/http://danceplus.co.in/judges-hosts-contestants-dance-plus-2015/ |archive-date=28 July 2015 |website=Dance Plus TV Show |access-date=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n* ''[[Dance Plus (season 2)|Dance Plus]]'', Season 2 (2016)\n* ''[[Dance Plus (season 3)|Dance Plus]]'', Season 3 (2017)\n* ''[[Dance Champions]]'' with [[Terence Lewis (choreographer)|Terrence Lewis]] (2017)\n* ''[[Dance Plus (season 4)|Dance Plus]]'', Season 4 (2018-19)\n* ''[[Dance Plus (season 5)|Dance Plus]]'', Season 5 (2019-20)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{National Film Award Best Choreography}}\n{{Filmfare Award for Best Choreography}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:D'Souza, Remo}}\n[[Category:Indian choreographers]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian male dancers]]\n[[Category:Popping dancers]]\n[[Category:Dancers from Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Artists from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Best Choreography National Film Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Remo D'Souza\n| image         = Remo d souza did final.jpg\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Ramesh Gopi <ref>{{cite web |last=Mishra |first=Rashmi |title=Remo D\u2019Souza aka Ramesh Gopi: Top 9 celebrities and their real names |url=https://www.india.com/buzz/remo-dsouza-aka-ramesh-gopi-top-9-celebrities-and-their-real-names-26079/ |date=24 March 2014 |website=India.com |access-date=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1974|04|02|df=yes}}\n| birth_place   = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| nationality   = [[India]]n\n| occupation    = [[Choreographer]], [[film director]], [[film actor]], [[Film producer|producer]]\n| spouse        = Lizelle D'Souza\n| children      = \n| parents       = K. Gopi<br />Madhvi Laxmi \n| image size    = \n| yearsactive   = 1995\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Remo D'Souza''' (born '''Ramesh Gopi'''<ref>{{cite news |title=Do you know Remo D'Souza's real name? |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Do-you-know-Remo-DSouzas-real-name/articleshow/32541291.cms |date=23 March 2014 |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |agency=[[Asian News International]] |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref> on 2 April 1974) is an Indian dancer, choreographer, actor and film director.\n\n==Personal life==\nD'Souza hails from [[Olavakkode]], [[Palakkad]], [[Kerala]], and was born on April 2, 1974 in [[Bangalore]] to K. Gopi, a chef in the Indian Air Force, and Madhvi Laxmi. He has an elder brother, Ganesh Gopi, and four sisters. He did his schooling at the Air Force School, [[Jamnagar]], [[Gujarat]]. During his school days, he was an athlete and won prizes in the 100 meter race.<ref>{{Citation |last=Asian Paints |title=Har Ghar Kucch Kehta Hai -  Ninth Episode Remo D'Souza |date=2013-12-26 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O3DsH5VXh3Q |accessdate=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\nHe is married to Lizelle, an Anglo-Indian from [[Mumbai]]. Lizelle is a costume designer who has designed costumes for many television shows. They have two sons, Dhruv and Gabriel. Currently Souza lives with his family, in [[Andheri West]], [[Mumbai]].{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n==Career==\nD'Souza was a judge in the show ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' (DID) with [[Terence Lewis (choreographer)|Terence Lewis]] and [[Geeta Kapoor]] , ''Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa'' with the Indian actress [[Madhuri Dixit]] and director [[Karan Johar]]. He was the \"super judge\" on the prime time dance show ''[[Dance Plus]]'', on Star Plus, along with team captains [[Dharmesh Yelande]], [[Shakti Mohan]], and [[Punit Pathak]]. Currently{{when|date=December 2017}} he is appearing as a judge on the reality show ''[[Dance Champions]]'' opposite [[Terence Lewis (choreographer)|Terence Lewis]].\n\nHis first movie as a director, ''[[F.A.L.T.U]]'', was a moderate success at the box office.\n\nHe made India's first 3D dance movie, ''[[AnyBody Can Dance - ABCD|ABCD - AnyBody Can Dance]]'', with contestants from [[Dance India Dance#Season 1|season 1]] and [[Dance India Dance#Season 2|season 2]] of ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' ([[Dharmesh Yelande]], [[Punit Pathak]], [[Salman Yusuff Khan]], [[Raghav Juyal]], Prince and others), [[Prabhu Deva]] and [[Lauren Gottlieb]]. His next directorial venture, ''ABCD 2'', was released in June 2015. It starred [[Varun Dhawan]], [[Shraddha Kapoor]], and [[Prabhu Deva]] in lead roles, with [[Lauren Gottlieb]], [[Punit Pathak]], [[Raghav Juyal]], and [[Dharmesh Yelande]] in supporting roles.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |title=\u2018ABCD 2\u2032: Varun Dhawan plays Suresh from Fictitious Dance Academy |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/abcd-2-varun-dhawan-plays-suresh-from-fictitious-dance-academy/ |date=2015 |newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=26 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Shraddha Kapoor injures herself while dancing for ABCD 2 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Hindi/Bollywood/News/Shraddha-Kapoor-injures-herself-while-dancing-for-ABCD-2/articleshow/39288650.cms |date=30 July 2014 |newspaper=The Times of India |access-date=5 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n! colspan=\"6\" |Film awards\n|-\n!Year\n!Film\n!Award\n!Category\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n|2004\n|[[Tehzeeb (2003 film)|''Tehzeeb'']] \n|[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|Best Choreography\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Enthiran]]''\n|[[Vijay Awards]]\n|Best Find of the Year\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Student of the Year]]''\n|[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|Best Choreography <small>(For the song \"Disco Deewane\")</small>\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2014\n| rowspan=\"5\" |''[[Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani]]''\n|[[Screen Awards]]\n|Best Choreography <small>(for the song \"Badtameez Dil\")</small>\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|Best Choreography <small>(for the song \"Badtameez Dil\")</small>\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n|Best Choreography <small>(for the song \"Badtameez Dil\")</small>\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Producers Guild Film Awards|Producer's Guild Film Awards]]\n|Best Choreography <small>(for the song \"Badtameez Dil\")</small>\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Best Choreography <small>(for the song \"Balam Pichkari\")</small>\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"10\" |2016\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''[[ABCD 2|Anybody Can Dance 2]]''\n|[[BIG Star Entertainment Awards]]\n|Most Entertaining Social Film\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Stardust Awards]]\n|Best Choreography <small>(for all songs of ''ABCD 2'')</small>\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Screen Awards]]\n|Best Choreography <small>(for the song \"Sunn Saathiya\")</small>\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n